<item>
            <title>[LU-19473] nid_addr_is_set false negatives</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19473</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Numeric based NIDs can have address &quot;0&quot;. This causes problems for nid_addr_is_set() which can only look for a non-zero address value.&lt;br/&gt;
This causes two bugs:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If a node has multiple NIDs on one net, one of the NIDs has a 0&lt;br/&gt;
       address, then an attempt to delete the 0 address NID will cause&lt;br/&gt;
       all NIDs on the network to be removed.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If the source NID specified for lnetctl ping has a 0 address then&lt;br/&gt;
       this is not correctly passed down to the kernel (so the ping is&lt;br/&gt;
       processed as though no souce NID were specified).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
